H0.text: What trade takes its name from the old word for twelve dozen. Baker

H1.text: What trade takes its name from the old word for twelve dozen. Merchant

H2.text: What trade takes its name from the old word for twelve dozen. Trader

H3.text: What trade takes its name from the old word for twelve dozen. Grocer

A4.text: Because these items were often bought in bulk, they were named after the French word for wholesaler, or 'grossier'.

A5.text: 'gross' (meaning a quantity of 12 dozen, or 144) is also derived from the Medieval Latin term 'grossarius'.
